oai_dc:dc.dc:title: PHOTOGRAMMETRIC MONITORING OF DOLOS STABILITY, MANASQUAN INLET, NEW JERSEY
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Gebert, Jeffrey A.
Clausner, James
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: photogrammetric monitoring
dolos
dolos stability
Manasquan Inlet
New Jersey
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Photogrammetry has been applied as a technique to monitor the stability of dolosse on the Manasquan Inlet, New Jersey jetties. These jetties were rehabilitated between 1979 and 1982 with 16-ton steel-reinforced dolosse. The jetties have been exposed to a number of storms since 1982, including a design-level storm in March 1984. The photogrammetric measurements have provided a detailed record of the magnitude and direction of dolos movements in response to these storm events. Standard leveling techniques have been used to check the accuracy of the elevation data derived from photogrammetry. This paper describes the methods used in this monitoring effort and the results obtained from the photogrammetric measurements. Also presented are data on the structural integrity of the steelreinforced dolosse.
